Duration: 20h57m22s

......::::: Bio & Info :::::......

The trance polish artist Krzysztof PrÃ„â„¢tkiewicz, best known as Nitrous Oxide, in 1998 discovered the opportunity to create music using his personal computer. From a simple hobby it became soon a real passion and in 2005 he released his first song Galaxia.
In a short time he started new projects and collaborations (3rd Moon, Husaria, Silver Mist) and soon his talent was noticed by other artists such as Above & Beyond, who, in 2006, "recruit" him under their own label Anjunabeats, so Oxide could published his first EP North Pole / Frozen Dreams.
After producing upliftin' single such as Red Moon Slide, for the first time he decided to create vocal tunes relying on the voice of Aneym, producing Far Away and Follow You, that claimed the talent of the artist on the trance scene. These singles withvinced him to produce his first album Dreamcatcher, released in 2010.

This release includes all the tracks (also the self-released ones) composed with the aliases Nitrous Oxide, 3rd Moon, N2O, Husaria, Silver Mist, Redmoon and Bunny Deluxe.

Hope this amazing genre will spread more and more and will get the approvation it deserves!
